Subject: [PATCH] flists: make tidelink_top_full_asic_v2 elaborate (V2 = the ship config)

Repo:  tidelink  (git.soton.ac.uk / SoC-Labs mirror)
Apply: from the tidelink repo root:  git apply 0004-...patch
       (or:  patch -p1 < 0004-...patch)
File:  flists/tidelink_top_full_asic_v2.flist

WHY
---
tidelink_top_full_asic_v2.flist — the flist that selects the V2 GPIO-PHY, i.e.
the configuration we ship — had never elaborated. `vcs -f <resolved v2 flist>
-top tidelink_top` produced three errors. The V1 flist (tidelink_top_full_asic)
is untouched by this patch and stays bit-identical.

1. Error-[IND] TIDELINK_SYNC_PERIOD / TIDELINK_SYNC_WORD not declared
   (tidelink_phy_sync_insert.sv:33,35)

   tidelink_sync_word.svh declares the two constants and guards itself with
   `ifndef TIDELINK_SYNC_WORD_SVH. Whichever file includes it FIRST decides the
   scope they land in:

     * tidelink_lane_deskew*.sv     includes it at $unit scope  (line 162/184)
     * tidelink_phy_sync_detect.sv  includes it at $unit scope  (line 83)
     * WavD2DGpio*.v                includes it INSIDE the module (line 887/966)

   sync_insert/_detect need them at $unit for their parameter defaults. The V2
   ASIC flist compiled WavD2DGpio_v2.v (line 127) long before any deskew (line
   269), so WavD2DGpio_v2 set the include guard while binding the constants to
   module scope, and every later $unit include became a no-op.

   tidelink_fpga_v2.flist does not have this bug: it lists the deskew at 152,
   ahead of WavD2DGpio_v2 at 165. This patch adopts that order.

2. Error-[CFCILFBI] cannot find cell 'tidelink_phy_sync_detect'

   The header said sync_detect was "NOT included (deliberate)". That note
   predates the R-A local override: WavD2DGpio_v2.v:863 INSTANTIATES
   tidelink_phy_sync_detect (u_rx_sync_detect), so it is mandatory, not
   optional. fpga_v2 already lists it (line 180). Header note corrected.

3. Cross-lane deskew: ASIC shipped a different module than FPGA validated

   Not an elaboration error — worse. asic_v2 bound
   deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_lane_deskew.sv while fpga_v2 binds
   src/rtl/local_overrides/tidelink_lane_deskew_v2.sv. Same module name,
   different RTL. The override carries the F3c IDLE-ZERO sync_hit qualifier
   (2026-07-02): at SYNC_REANCHOR_TOL=5, lane 0's SYNC slice 0x1F00 has
   popcount 5 == TOL, so an all-zero inter-packet IDLE word is a
   within-tolerance "match" on lane 0; the anti-poison self-gating then sees a
   CONTINUOUS match, `periodic` never asserts, and lane 0 can never commit
   sync_seen on a quiet link. Sim-proven (test_31 F3: slave sync_seen_vec stuck
   0xFE, lane 0 alone missing) and consistent with the silicon zero-poke
   "sync_seen_vec sparse" observation.

   The fix exists on NO tidelink-phy branch (checked every remote head at
   bbd094c) — the local override is its only carrier, by design ("submodule
   copy stays pristine"). So as it stood, the ASIC build would have taped out a
   deskew the FPGA link validation never ran. This patch binds the override,
   matching fpga_v2.

VERIFIED
--------
  vcs -full64 -sverilog -f <resolved v2 flist> -top tidelink_top   -> exit 0
  (rf_16k.v macro sim model appended for the VCS run only; Genus links the
  .lib. No same-name module is defined twice: WavD2DGpio, WlinkGPIOPHY,
  tidelink_lane_deskew, tidelink_phy_align_calibrator, tidelink_lane_checker
  each resolve to exactly one file.)

NOTE
----
V2 also needs the deps/tidelink-phy submodule, which was registered but never
initialised. Its .gitmodules remote is SSH (git@git.soton.ac.uk) on branch
feat/phy-refactor, while the pinned commit bbd094c sits on recon-phy-pin —
worth reconciling upstream.

diff --git a/flists/tidelink_top_full_asic_v2.flist b/flists/tidelink_top_full_asic_v2.flist
index 5e7805d..3fcc283 100644
--- a/flists/tidelink_top_full_asic_v2.flist
+++ b/flists/tidelink_top_full_asic_v2.flist
@@ -26,11 +26,12 @@
 // tidelink_phy_sync_insert IS now included (2026-06-15): the DEFAULT-OFF LL
 // re-hunt beacon inserter sits in the WavD2DGpio TX path, gated by APB
 // SWI_SYNC_INSERT_EN (Region 8 slot 0 bit[2], 0x4403_2100) which resets 0 ->
-// pure passthrough / bit-identical until SW opts in. NOT included (deliberate):
-// tidelink_gpio_phy_rx/tx wrappers, tidelink_phy_sync_detect (RX SYNC strip is
-// the intact WlinkRxLinkLayer path) and the BIST files — the silicon-proven
-// composition (PHY-BIST core) puts the checker + calibrator at controller
-// level on the 128-bit link data.
+// pure passthrough / bit-identical until SW opts in. tidelink_phy_sync_detect
+// IS ALSO included (2026-07-16): the R-A local override WavD2DGpio_v2.v
+// instantiates it directly, so it is mandatory — see the note at its line.
+// NOT included (deliberate): tidelink_gpio_phy_rx/tx wrappers and the BIST
+// files — the silicon-proven composition (PHY-BIST core) puts the checker +
+// calibrator at controller level on the 128-bit link data.
 // =============================================================================
 +define+TIDELINK_PHY_V2
 +incdir+${TIDELINK_HOME}/src/rtl
@@ -117,6 +118,25 @@ ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WavAnd.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WavClockGate.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WavClockInv.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WavClockMux.v
+// Cross-lane word deskew. MUST be compiled BEFORE WavD2DGpio_v2.v below: this
+// file `includes tidelink_sync_word.svh at $unit scope, which is what declares
+// TIDELINK_SYNC_WORD / TIDELINK_SYNC_PERIOD for the parameter defaults of
+// tidelink_phy_sync_insert / _detect. WavD2DGpio*.v also includes the header,
+// but from INSIDE the module — so if it compiles first it sets the header's
+// include guard while binding the constants to module scope, and the later
+// $unit includes become no-ops (Error-[IND] identifier not declared). Same
+// order as tidelink_fpga_v2.flist.
+// F3c LOCAL OVERRIDE (2026-07-02): the deps copy is replaced by
+// src/rtl/local_overrides/tidelink_lane_deskew_v2.sv — identical except the
+// sync_hit idle-zero qualifier (lane-0 slice 0x1F00 popcount==TOL(5) made
+// all-zero IDLE words continuously "match", starving the periodic confirm →
+// sync_seen never commits on a quiet link). Submodule copy stays pristine, and
+// the fix exists on no tidelink-phy branch, so this file is its only carrier.
+// Keep in lockstep with tidelink_fpga_v2.flist — the ASIC build must not ship
+// a deskew the FPGA link validation never ran.
+// # Comment-out original: ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_lane_deskew.sv
+${TIDELINK_HOME}/src/rtl/local_overrides/tidelink_lane_deskew_v2.sv
+
 // V2 PHY SWAP: serdes lane fork from the shared PHY component (FIX-N..R,
 // silicon-validated 2026-06-10) replaces src/rtl/local_overrides/{WavD2DGpio,
 // WavD2DGpioRx,WavD2DGpioTx}.v. Same module names — never co-compile with V1.
@@ -135,6 +155,13 @@ ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_phy_tx_mask.sv
 // inserter instantiated inside WavD2DGpio TX path. Bit-identical with APB
 // enable=0; includes tidelink_sync_word.svh via +incdir .../deps/tidelink-phy/rtl.
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_phy_sync_insert.sv
+// SoC Labs RX mask-aware SYNC-beacon DETECT: instantiated inside WavD2DGpio_v2
+// on the post-deskew word (u_rx_sync_detect, WavD2DGpio_v2.v:863), so it is
+// NOT optional here. The header's "NOT included (deliberate)" note above
+// predates the R-A local override that added the instance, and leaving it out
+// is what produced Error-[CFCILFBI] "cannot find cell tidelink_phy_sync_detect".
+// Pure read-side observability — datapath bit-identical (sync_en_i tied 1).
+${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_phy_sync_detect.sv
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_phy_rx_demask.sv
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WavDemetReset.v
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/axi-chiplet-controller/logical/wlink/WavDemetReset_107.v
@@ -264,9 +291,9 @@ ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_popcount16.sv
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_lane_checker_single.sv
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_lane_checker.sv
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_gpio_phy_apb_regs.sv
-// Cross-lane word deskew — V2 PHY SWAP: shared-component copy (instantiated
-// by the new WavD2DGpio with its own depth/offset handling).
-${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_lane_deskew.sv
+// Cross-lane word deskew is compiled EARLIER in this file (before
+// WavD2DGpio_v2.v) — it must declare the sync-word constants at $unit scope
+// first. See the comment there.
 // V2 PHY SWAP: new lane-mask-aware calibrator (S_PROBE/eye-centre + M8/M9/M11
 // lineage + FIX-E/H/J hooks) replaces src/rtl/tidelink_phy_align_calibrator.sv.
 ${TIDELINK_HOME}/deps/tidelink-phy/rtl/tidelink_phy_align_calibrator.sv
